Kubernetes commands
-------------------

1.It will display the all the pods
 
$ kubectl get pods --all-nampspaces
$ kubectl get pods

2. Display the pod information 

 $ kubectl describe pod -n <namespace>  <name>

3. How to apply the file

 $ kubectl apply -f <file name >
 $ kubectl apply -f nginx-ser.yaml 
 $  kubectl apply -f nginx-ser.yaml --dry-run

4. How to delete the file 
  
 $ kubectl delete -f nginx-ser.yaml 

5. see the only services 

 $ kubectl get svc

6. Display the all pods, svc, deploy

 $ kubectl get po,svc,deploy,ingress

7. Display the PersistentVolume

 $ kubectl get pv (or) rc 

8. $ kubectl run -it --rm --image=mysql:5.6 --restart=Never mysql-client --mysql -h mysql -ppassword

9. Delete pod

  $ kubectl delete pod <name>
